race.comment: Good little contest with some progressive types engaged. STEEL KNIGHT (4) resumes in a much easier contest after he covered plenty of ground in the run when last in the LR Mitchell McKenzie Stakes over 1200m at Moonee Valley last September. Fitted with the two trials and hard to hold out with the claim. IRON FURY (3) will be at his peak for this, and he gets a much better setup today. Stalked the speed and strong through the line when second over 1100m at Gosford. Proven at this track and no excuses here. FERINZO (6) talented gelding returning from a lengthy break. Created a big impression over the Grafton carnival when a slick 3 len Maiden winner on July 18, 2024. Fitted with the two trials and should be primed for this. PERLE DE CHOCOLAT (8) returns from a let-up. Covered ground in the run and failed to close off when a poor seventh over 1200m at Kembla Grange. Since fitted with a 900m tick over trial and has a host of gear changes from the inside gate. Improver.
